'Phe segmentation of the ovum.

All that is known with regard to the phenomena of segmentation in the eggs of Clypeastroids is confined to the »Preliminary Observations» on the development of Echinarachnius by FEWKEs. However, seeing that his description is brief and evidently not based on investigations of the segmentation of the same ovum, and that, besides, the pheno- mena of segmentation in Echinocyamus differ essentially in several respects from those in Echinaxachnius, it will not be out of place if I communicate the results of my own investigatione a little more in de- tail.
